<h2>Unlockable Characters</h2>

<p>The main campaign pairs Sonic and Tails, but completing the game opens up three additional characters — each one changes how you approach the zones.</p>

<div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:12px;margin:20px 0 32px">
<div class="details-box" style="margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column">
<h3 style="font-size:1.2em;margin:0 0 8px">Knuckles</h3>
<p style="margin:0;font-size:0.95em;line-height:1.5;flex:1">Unlocked after beating the main campaign. Gets <strong>exclusive routes</strong> in every zone, his own boss fights (including a unique final boss added in v1.1.0), and an Angel Island prologue. Uses the Air Necklace for extended underwater sections instead of the submarine.</p>
</div>
<div class="details-box" style="margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column">
<h3 style="font-size:1.2em;margin:0 0 8px">Metal Sonic</h3>
<p style="margin:0;font-size:0.95em;line-height:1.5;flex:1">Unlocked after clearing the game with Knuckles. Features a <strong>damaging hover</strong> with an electric shield effect while airborne. Trades some of Sonic's abilities for unique aerial offense. Available in Free Play mode.</p>
</div>
<div class="details-box" style="margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column">
<h3 style="font-size:1.2em;margin:0 0 8px">Fang the Sniper</h3>
<p style="margin:0;font-size:0.95em;line-height:1.5;flex:1">Unlocked by collecting all Chaos Emeralds. A <strong>run-and-gun character</strong> with a triple jump and pistol shots — a completely different playstyle for Sonic. Available in Free Play mode.</p>
</div>
</div>

<h2>Special Stages and the True Final Boss</h2>

<p>Hidden Giant Rings throughout the zones lead to <strong>Special Stages built as races against Fang</strong>. You collect rings to extend your timer and grab lightning bolts to shock and slow him down, while navigating branching obstacle courses where every fork forces a choice: gain more time, or sabotage your rival? They start manageable but escalate fast — Fang gets quicker and the margins get tighter with each emerald. The community considers them among the best Special Stages in any Sonic game, right alongside CD and Mania.</p>

<p>Collecting all six Chaos Emeralds (Eggman holds the seventh until the end) and reaching the finale unlocks the <strong>true final boss: a four-phase battle against Metal Sonic in space</strong>. Metal steals the negative energy from the Emeralds and transforms into increasingly massive forms — including one based on the <strong>unused Metal Sonic Mark III design from Sonic X-Treme</strong>. The fight demands 30 hits across all phases, with the scenery dynamically descending from orbit to just above the ocean surface. It ends with a beam struggle that feels straight out of Dragon Ball Z. Fans widely consider it <strong>one of the most ambitious final encounters in any classic-style Sonic game</strong>.</p>

<h2>Sonic Triple Trouble 16-Bit FAQ</h2>

<div class="details-grid">
<details>
<summary>Is Sonic Triple Trouble 16-Bit free?</summary>
<p>Yes, completely free. Available for Windows (32 and 64-bit), macOS, and Android — including legacy systems like Windows 98/XP.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Do I need to play the original Game Gear version?</summary>
<p>No. This is a standalone experience that expands on the original in every way. You can jump in with zero prior knowledge of the 1994 game.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How do I unlock all characters?</summary>
<p>Beat the main campaign to unlock Knuckles. Beat it again as Knuckles to unlock Metal Sonic. Collect all Chaos Emeralds to unlock Fang the Sniper.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Can I use Super Sonic?</summary>
<p>Only on a completed save file. The seventh Chaos Emerald is held by Eggman until the final boss, so Super Sonic is not available on a first playthrough.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How does character swapping work?</summary>
<p>During the main campaign, one button switches instantly between Sonic and Tails in real time. Tails can fly to reach hidden areas, while Sonic is faster with more offensive moves.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Does it have multiplayer?</summary>
<p>Yes. A competition mode features multiple game types and its own single-player tournament campaign. Note that the mode was somewhat buggy at launch and continues to receive updates.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>What are the system requirements?</summary>
<p>Extremely low. The game was built to run on hardware as old as Windows 98 and legacy Android devices. Any modern PC or smartphone will have no issues.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is there a true final boss?</summary>
<p>Yes. Collect all Chaos Emeralds and complete the game to face a four-phase battle against Metal Sonic as Super Sonic in space — widely regarded as one of the best final bosses in any Sonic fangame.</p>
</details>
</div>
